Netherlands Supports Financial Transaction Tax, Rutte Says

-- B y   M a r t i j n   v a n   d e r   S t a r r e
-- 
2011-10-22T15:30:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-22/netherlands-supports-financial-transaction-tax-rutte-says.html
The Netherlands supports a financial
transaction tax.  “The cabinet supports such a tax,” Prime Minister  Mark
Rutte  said in parliament in The Hague today. “But we aren’t
supporters of an introduction in only a few countries because
the effects could then be enormous,” he also said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Martijn van der Starre at 
 vanderstarre@bloomberg.net  